    • Class org.latency4j.WorkDuration extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      8781195826267188958L

      • Serialized Fields

        • start

          long start

          System timestamp denoting the start of the task to which the instance relates.

        • end

          long end

          System timestamp denoting the end of the task to which the instance relates.

        • root

          boolean root

          A boolean that denotes if the the method to which the instance relates is the lowest in the call stack with respect to the sequence of operation executions which, together, compose the task being performed.

        • errored

          boolean errored

          Indicates if the operation to which the instance relates failed with an exception or not.

        • methodName

          java.lang.String methodName

          The name of the method from which the instance is generated. This is the method from which the related operation is initiated.

        • error

          java.lang.Throwable error

          Where a task is terminated by an exception, this field holds a reference to the exception.

        • identifier

          WorkDurationId identifier

          The instance identifier.

    • Class org.latency4j.WorkDurationId extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      -4887858866762134439L

      • Serialized Fields

        • workCategory

          java.lang.String workCategory

          The category of the task to which the duration instance relates. Put differently, this is the requirement category which covers the operation or task for which the duration instance was generated.

        • threadId

          java.lang.String threadId

          The id/name of the thread in which duration is generated. This is thread in which the monitored operation is performed or executed, thus leading to a duration.
